tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient"s labs are largely within normal limits. Notable findings include a mildly decreased HbA1c, which may suggest recent hypoglycemia or anemia, and a low creatinine, likely reflecting reduced muscle mass common in elderly patients rather than renal dysfunction. No acute metabolic or electrolyte disturbances are evident. Clinical correlation is recommended.
